review:
Quake 3 Arena is timeless and not much more can be written about it. Here's some no mods required custom/wide screen resolution instructions I found. Just slightly modified the original wording from the link below. Make sure to see tip #2 about using an autoexec.cfg file. Mind your //'s if you're reading this review and blindly copying and pasting -- it just comments the line out so anything after it won't be read. 

// Wide Screen/Custom Resolution Instructions from: https://www.wsgf.org/dr/quake-iii-arena

// For Quake 3 Arena purchased via Steam, the correct config file should be: 
// Steam\SteamApps\common\quake 3 arena\baseq3\q3config.cfg (for Quake 3 Arena)
// Steam\SteamApps\common\quake 3 arena\missionpack\q3config.cfg (for Quake 3 Team //Arena)

// For Quake 3 Arena purchased via store media, the correct config file should be: 
// C:\Program Files\Quake 3 Arena\baseq3\q3config.cfg (for Quake 3 Arena)
// C:\Program Files\Quake 3 Arena\missionpack\q3config.cfg (for Quake 3 Team Arena)

// 2) Other tip is you may create an autoexec.cfg file on each subdirectory [baseq3 and //missionpack] and put the below settings in there
// because Quake 3 may reset the q3config.cfg if you change something via game menu.

seta r_mode "-1" 

// Set this to -1.

seta r_customwidth "1920" 
seta r_customheight "1080" 

// Set this to your favorite widescreen resolution.

seta cg_fov "105" 

// Set this according to your preference. I recommend 100 for 16:10 resolutions and 105 for //16:9 resolutions.
